stateful vs stateless
https://social.msdn.microsoft.com/Forums/vstudio/en-US/4f0fd4ba-ca04-4353-ab10-9da0c58f60b5/stateless-class-in-c?forum=csharpgeneral
A stateless/immutable class is said to be stateless when it doesn't have any mutators (or fields at all).
a class must not have fields to be stateless.
